history.text: Hi
Hello
Have you seen Iron Man
I have seen Iron Man.
Did you like it
I did like it.  It was a great movie.  I thoroughly enjoyed it.
I know it was! I love how Robert Downey Jr. acts
his just too funny
He is very good actor.  He is indeed very funny.  It is funny how he uses his wit whenever he is making conversation and trying to relay his point or his ideas.
What is your favorite part of the movie?
Yeah, he portrays a great image
just doesnt care what people think about them
my favorite part is when Tony is captive by the Ten Rings leader
Raz
Raza
That was a very good part.  It is funny how he uses his mind when he overcome problems that he is faced with in the movie.
Yeah it is! it was a tough one to get out of
what was your favorite part?
My favorite part is when he is in the cave trying to come up with the equipment to make his prototype iron man suit.  It was a beginning to something greater and more profound for him.
I tell you I liked Jeff Bridges role in the movie as well.
That was a great part! I also liked it,
and he was a cool supervillain,
what  do you think about the reviews of the movie

I thought the reviews of the movie were good.  I believe that in light of the rotten tomatoe scores today, it probably would have been significantly higher.  I am not sure what the rotten tomatoe score was then, but I know today that it would been higher in light of all of the other super hero movies that have come out since.
What part did you dislike the most about the movie?
Yeah, I think CinemaScore is accurate,
I disliked the actor that plays James Rhodes
I think the new actor is better for the part
and didnt like the one from the first part

Well, I am not very familiar with CinemaScore rating system.  Well, I do agree about the acting choice for James Rhodes.  I do like Don Cheadle in the role better than Terrance Howard. I believe that Terrence Howard is a great actor but that particular role probably was not meant for him in particular.  I would say definitely aces for Don Cheadle in the role for War Machine going forward which is great.
Did you like the director of the film?
What do you think of Jon Favreay
Favreau*

I know for me as far as dislikes in the movie.  I did not like the idea that Tony was captured in the middle of the movie and then forced to use his mental prowess to overcome the escape. I guess that that part was bittersweet for me.

Oh, Tony's sidekick, Jon Favreau.  I thought that he was great.  It is funny I can remember him specifically from Iron Man 2 but my memory in the first one is a little sketchy.  But I am not sure that he did a great job.  He is a good actor.  He always has Tony's back.
Oh I thought you liked that part!
I  meant the Director of the movie lol Jon Favreau
I think the movie has good special effects considering it came out on 2008
and its the first Avengers movie
The director of the movie is also the one how played the role of Tony's side kick in Iron Man 2.  The special effects were first rate back then.  They did a great job in the process.
I didnt know! thats a great fact,

That is true.  It is considered as many people would say the first Avengers movie because it is a part of the Phase One process for Marvel back then.  It is amazing how they are on the third phase of the process with the new Avengers movie coming out in the next couple of months.
Yeah, it is! I love the other Marvel movies
a lot of good tittles
all starting with Iron Man
Well, thank you.  Jon Favreau have been around for quite some time.  He is a great actor as well as a great director.
I saw that you had left.  Are you coming back?   Or is that the end?  Please advise.

uid2response.feedback: I have enjoyed watching Iron Man. I believe that the conversation will warrant another viewing of the movie.
